scenarios.prompt:
Extend the following existing function to also handle arrays — if the input is an array, return the results of formatting each element joined with ', '. All existing behavior for non-array inputs must remain unchanged.

```js
// Format a number as a USD currency string
// Handles: integers, floats, negative values
function formatCurrency(amount) {
  if (typeof amount !== 'number' || isNaN(amount)) {
    throw new TypeError('amount must be a number');
  }
  const sign = amount < 0 ? '-' : '';
  const abs = Math.abs(amount);
  return `${sign}$${abs.toFixed(2)}`;
}

module.exports = { formatCurrency };
```

Assumptions already confirmed: extend in-place, Node.js CommonJS, no external packages needed.
